response.caption: Rigging in Blender is kinda weird! But, It’s not so bad once I got used to how the IK’s worked in Blender vs Maya (Maya’s just feels…easier in this regard). I didn’t really bother to weight paint past the tail because this is a pretty basic model, but I was hoping to put some sort of physics on the bow. But…I forget what it’s called to have it sort of sway with the head via physics instead of me manually putting it in. Anyways, Physics is my next step.
